# Cursor Lifecycle Routing

## Canonical Routing Input

- `.cursor/docs/INDEX.md` (single routing narrative)

## Intent to Stage Mapping

- Think: architecture questions, constraints, tradeoff discovery
- Plan: phased design, sequencing, dependency analysis
- Build: concrete code changes in `src/` or `frontend/src/`
- Review: risk/bug/regression checks
- Test: parity, replay, and module validation
- Ship: commit hygiene and release readiness

## Stage-to-Docs Routing

Use `.cursor/docs/INDEX.md` as the single lifecycle routing narrative.
Open other docs and skills only when routed by that index.
Ship stage must follow `.cursor/commands/3-pre-commit-workflow.md`.

## Routing Rules

- Use the narrowest stage that satisfies the request.
- If request spans multiple stages, complete them in lifecycle order.
- Treat `.cursor/docs/*` as canonical docs before root mirror docs.
- Keep `.cursor/docs/API_ENDPOINTS.md` usage limited to endpoint parity compatibility.
